    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-04-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-09-27T19:52:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Homeless Veterans Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2004 - Extends through FY 2008 the authority of the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to make grants to furnish the following assistance to homeless veterans: (1) outreach; (2) rehabilitative services; (3) vocational counseling and training; and (4) transitional housing.</p> <p>Increases and extends through FY 2008 the authorization of appropriations for homeless assistance to veterans furnished through the Department of Veterans Affairs.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>17</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-06-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-09-27T19:54:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Homeless Veterans Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2004 - Extends through FY 2008 the authority of the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to make grants to furnish the following assistance to homeless veterans: (1) outreach; (2) rehabilitative services; (3) vocational counseling and training; and (4) transitional housing.</p> <p>Increases and extends through FY 2008 the authorization of appropriations for homeless assistance to veterans furnished through the Department of Veterans Affairs.</p> <p>Makes permanent (currently, terminates on December 31, 2004) the authority of the Secretary to provide sexual trauma counseling and appropriate care and services to veterans.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>36</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-10-07</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-05-09T20:34:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Homeless Veterans Assistance Act of 2004 - Increases the authorization of appropriations for FY 2005 for homeless assistance to veterans furnished through the Department of Veterans Affairs.</p> <p>Makes permanent (current law terminates on December 31, 2004) the authority of the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to provide sexual trauma counseling and appropriate care and services to veterans.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
